        <div>
            <pb facs="#TL-0461.jpg" n="part3_p069.jpg" xml:id="img_0069" corresp="https://id.acdh.oeaw.ac.at/tillich-lectures/part3_p069.jpg"/>
            
            <p facs="#facs_69_tr_1">
               <lb facs="#facs_69_tr_1_tl_1" n="N001"/>-ame¬
               <lb facs="#facs_69_tr_1_tl_2" n="N002"/>This brings me to a point to which I referred: family and sex. Most of these things are
               <lb facs="#facs_69_tr_1_tl_3" n="N003"/>produced NOT DIRECTLy by ministers,Vhrches, public opinion, but the SEEDS almost always
               <lb facs="#facs_69_tr_1_tl_4" n="N004"/>go back to the family, because in the family situation the first forming attempts are made and are
               <lb facs="#facs_69_tr_1_tl_5" n="N005"/>more successful than any other later attempt for education—we should never forget this. It is not
               <lb facs="#facs_69_tr_1_tl_6" n="N006"/>because [of] the special form of family life, it is not the bourgeois Comily life, with the
               <lb facs="#facs_69_tr_1_tl_7" n="N007"/>authoritarian father (in Europe) and the authoritarian mother (in America) [laughter], but it is
               <lb facs="#facs_69_tr_1_tl_8" n="N008"/>a natural structure, namely the immense dependence of the child, in earlier months and years, on
               <lb facs="#facs_69_tr_1_tl_9" n="N009"/>the parents or their representatives. Therefore the forming power of the family relation is tremendous.
               <lb facs="#facs_69_tr_1_tl_10" n="N010"/>Now in the family relation there are also implied the sex relations, first between the
            </p>
            <p facs="#facs_69_tr_3">
               <lb facs="#facs_69_tr_3_tl_1" n="N001"/>parents and then between the parents and the children, in the way in which death psychology has
               <lb facs="#facs_69_tr_3_tl_2" n="N002"/>descdaibed that, to a great extent, the successive power of the parents, if it is the mother, preventing
               <lb facs="#facs_69_tr_3_tl_3" n="N003"/>the sons from going to other women, to easily become housexuals, to become unable to love another
               <lb facs="#facs_69_tr_3_tl_4" n="N004"/> Coman, because thebondage which is partly based on the authority situation, (partly based on the
               <lb facs="#facs_69_tr_3_tl_5" n="N005"/>sex-relationship of the son to the mother, is so strong that many, many—1 know SO many psycho¬
               <lb facs="#facs_69_tr_3_tl_6" n="N006"/>analysts in this country, and the unanimous experience of them, whatever their theoretical attitude
               <lb facs="#facs_69_tr_3_tl_7" n="N007"/>besides it is that the ruin of so many good boys—potentially good and able to develop their good
            </p>
            <p facs="#facs_69_tr_2">
               <lb facs="#facs_69_tr_2_tl_1" n="N001"/>potentalities—is the bondage to a dominating mother and the INABILITY to get away from it.
               <lb facs="#facs_69_tr_2_tl_2" n="N002"/>Now this of course can be encarged to the father and the daughter, where we have very
               <lb facs="#facs_69_tr_2_tl_3" n="N003"/>similar situation. And all these situation demand a complete Revision in the light of these Coveries,
               <lb facs="#facs_69_tr_2_tl_4" n="N004"/>Monsieur
               <lb facs="#facs_69_tr_2_tl_5" n="N005"/>Monsieur Mʼa fois quʼil est vra lʼautre beaucoup
               <lb facs="#facs_69_tr_2_tl_6" n="N006"/>Cela nʼentraîne de cette fête
               <lb facs="#facs_69_tr_2_tl_7" n="N007"/>dʼune manière vieuse
               <lb facs="#facs_69_tr_2_tl_8" n="N008"/>dʼune manière beaucoup
               <lb facs="#facs_69_tr_2_tl_9" n="N009"/>G.C.H.P.
            </p>
            
        </div>
